Erin Dean https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Erin_Dean 0 Erin Jane Dean (born October 18, 1980) is an American actress. She is best known for her role as Robbie Stevenson in the television series The Journey of Allen Strange. She has also appeared in the feature films Lovers Lane and Lolita. On television, she has appeared in episodes of Boy Meets World, A Pig's Tale, Monty, Against the Grain, and Nickelodeon's game show Figure It Out. Dean began her acting career by performing stand-up comedy at 11 years of age around Hollywood and Beverly Hills. She won second place on America's Funniest People, which gained her Jeannine Cosden as her first and only agent. Erin has retired from acting and is said to have no plans of returning. She is now married and lives in Southern California with her husband who is a film audio editor. Erin_Jane_Dean ( born October_18_,_1980 ) is an_American_actress .
